criterion_text: Major surgery within 2 weeks before day 1.
No upper or lower respiratory infection within 4 weeks

Concurrent systemic treatment or prior therapy within 4 weeks for SMM

Cytostatic therapy / chemotherapy for cancer within the past 5 years
Women that underwent local radiation or chemotherapy within the last 12 months
Major surgery within 4 weeks prior to lymphodepleting chemotherapy.
Radiotherapy within the 2 weeks prior to initiation of treatment
Major surgery within 4 weeks of first dose of study drug
Any breast surgery or biopsy within the last 90 days
Major surgery within 21 days of starting protocol treatment
Receipt of any chemotherapy, biological therapy or investigational agents within 3 weeks prior to study registration
Major surgery within four weeks before consent date
Major surgery within 4 weeks
Chemotherapy or radiation treatment in the past six months
Prior pelvic radiotherapy or chemotherapy,
Major surgery other than diagnostic surgery =< 4 weeks prior to registration
Prior chemotherapy within the past 5 years
Surgery or chemotherapy within 4 weeks
Have undergone chemotherapy or radiation therapy within the previous one month
Chemotherapy within 3 weeks of the first scheduled study treatment
Had therapeutic radiation therapy or major surgery within 4 weeks before study drug treatment or palliative radiation therapy within 2 weeks before study drug treatment.
Major surgery within 14 days of starting study treatment
No other chemotherapy or radiation therapy within 14 days prior to registration
